{{Use South African English|date=August 2017}} {{Infobox book | name = How to Steal a City | author = Crispian Olver | language = English | country = South Africa | genre = Non-fiction, Autobiography, Memoir | published = Cape Town | publisher = [[Jonathan Ball Publishers]] | isbn = 9781868428205 | italic title = <!--(see above)--> | image = How_to_Steal_a_City.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = | cover_artist = | series = | release_number = | subject = [[Nelson Mandela Bay Metropolitan Municipality]], [[Local government]], [[Corruption in South Africa]], [[Politics of South Africa]] | set_in = Nelson Mandela Bay Metropolitan Municipality | publisher2 = | pub_date = 23 October 2017 | media_type = | pages = 280 | awards = | isbn_note = (Paperback) | oclc = | dewey = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
'''''How to Steal a City''''' (2017) is a book by Crispian Olver, a medical doctor and government official, from [[South Africa]]. The book is about the process of [[state capture]] and corruption within the [[Nelson Mandela Bay Metropolitan Municipality]], how it grew and efforts made by the government to fight it.<ref name="gr">{{Cite web |url=https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/36470081-how-to-steal-a-city |title=How to Steal a City |website=www.goodreads.com |access-date=2018-09-07}}</ref><ref name="iol">{{Cite web |url=https://www.iol.co.za/ios/behindthenews/review-insiders-guide-to-greed-and-factionalism-in-pe-11955478 |title=Review: Insider's guide to greed and factionalism in PE |publisher=Independent on Saturday |language=en |date=2018-11-11 |access-date=2018-09-07}}</ref><ref name="jb">{{Cite web |url=http://www.jonathanball.co.za/component/virtuemart/backlist-highlights-1/2017-releases-1/how-to-steal-a-city-detail?Itemid=6 |title=2017 Releases : How to Steal a City |last=JonathanBall.co.za |website=www.jonathanball.co.za |language=en-gb |access-date=2018-09-07}}</ref>
== Background and synopsis == In the book Olver alleges that the metro's government was controlled by a criminal syndicate closely associated with the [[African National Congress]] (ANC). The book details how the syndicate had build a sophisticated network of front companies, improper tenders, and network of corrupt local officials that the syndicate used to steal large amounts of public money from local government. The book concludes that the corruption, political divisions, and political disenchantment that the situation created led to the ANC losing the municipality in the [[South African municipal elections, 2016|2016 municipal elections]]. Despite the region being an ANC political stronghold in the past.<ref name="gr"/><ref name="iol" />
==Reception== The book was widely discussed in the media at the time of its publication.<ref name="n24">{{Cite web |url=https://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/how-to-steal-a-city-allegations-to-be-probed-20171023 |title='How to Steal a City' allegations to be probed |last=Nyoka |first=Nation |date=23 October 2017 |website=News24 |language=en |access-date=2018-09-07}}</ref><ref name="rc">{{Cite web |url=https://readinglist.click/sub/crispian-olver-discusses-his-book-how-to-steal-a-city-the-battle-for-nelson-mandela-bay/ |title=Crispian Olver discusses his book How to Steal a City: The Battle for Nelson Mandela Bay |website=readinglist.click |access-date=2018-09-07}}</ref> Kristoff Adelbert, Chief of Staff for Nelson Mandela Bay Metropolitan Municipality stated that all the allegations in the book would be investigated in an effort to fight corruption.<ref name="n24" />
