'''''The Syringa Tree''''' is a [[memory play]] of a childhood under [[apartheid]], written and often performed by [[Pamela Gien]], and directed by [[Larry Moss (acting coach)|Larry Moss]].<ref>[http://www.syringatree.com/syringa_tree.html?production=3 ''The Syringa Tree'' - Off Broadway<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060528232817/http://www.syringatree.com/syringa_tree.html?production=3 |date=2006-05-28 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.amrep.org/syringa/ Past Productions: ''The Syringa Tree''<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>  

It centers on the story of Elizabeth Grace, an English South African, and spans four generations.

